124.8	Mate_(beverage)	Mate (beverage)	Mate , also known as chimarrão (Portuguese: ) or cimarrón, is a traditional South American infused drink, particularly in Argentina, Uruguay, Paraguay, southern states of Brazil, south of Chile, the Bolivian Chaco, and to some extent, Syria and Lebanon. It is prepared from steeping dried leaves of yerba mate (llex paraguariensis, known in Portuguese as erva mate) in hot water.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Mate_en_calabaza.jpg/225px-Mate_en_calabaza.jpg
